# Undeadlock - Deadlock Detection Library

> **Master Repository:** `edamame_app` - See `../edamame_app/.cursor/rules/workspace.mdc` for workspace-wide rules.

## Project Overview

Light-weight diagnostic wrappers around `tokio::sync::RwLock`, `tokio::sync::Mutex`, and `dashmap::DashMap` that help discover lock contention and potential deadlocks during development.

In **debug** builds: Gathers runtime diagnostics (backtraces, timestamps, thread-ids) and logs warnings when locks are held too long.

In **release** builds: Zero overhead - types collapse to plain tokio/dashmap primitives.

## Key Types
- `CustomRwLock<T>` - Wrapper around `tokio::sync::RwLock`
- `CustomMutex<T>` - Wrapper around `tokio::sync::Mutex`
- `CustomDashMap<K, V>` - Wrapper around `dashmap::DashMap`

## Source Files
- `src/lib.rs` - Re-exports based on build mode
- `src/debug.rs` - Debug build implementation with diagnostics
- `src/release.rs` - Release build pass-through implementation

## Build & Test
```bash
cargo build                                    # Debug with diagnostics
cargo build --release                          # Release (zero overhead)
cargo test
cargo run --example basic_rwlock --features examples
```

## Default Thresholds (debug builds)
- Read lock warning: 10 seconds
- Write lock warning: 15 seconds
- Mutex lock warning: 15 seconds
- DashMap key held warning: 10 seconds

## Sampling Configuration
- Write operations: ~1% backtrace sampling (1 in 100)
- Read operations: No backtraces (performance)
- Timeouts: Always capture full diagnostics

## Usage
```rust
use undeadlock::{CustomRwLock, CustomMutex, CustomDashMap};

let lock = CustomRwLock::new(0u64);
let map = CustomDashMap::new("my_map");
```

